56
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:25,040
 The declaration, struct, date, star, pd says that pd is a pointer to a structure of type date, the notion exemplified by pd minus greater than year.

57
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:35,040
 I think I'll call that, at this point, pd right arrow, because that's really what it is. It's the minus greater than looks like an arrow to the right, so I'm going to call it right arrow, but it's really two characters.

