299
01:02:47,040 --> 01:02:53,040
 As an aside, hashing functions are one of the foundational notions in computer science.

300
01:02:53,040 --> 01:03:06,040
 Hashing functions are used for everything from high performance in memory structures, organizing databases, data, digital signing, network packet checksums, security algorithms, and much more.

301
01:03:06,040 --> 01:03:13,040
 The above text is a really great example of a really simple hashing function.

302
01:03:13,040 --> 01:03:30,040
 You should understand this simple presentation well so that when you encounter a more complex implementation or use of hashing, you can fall back on this text to understand that at its core hashing is a very simple concept.

303
01:03:30,040 --> 01:03:37,040
 So much of this chapter is a succinct example of some of the most powerful concepts in computer science.

