387
01:18:52,040 --> 01:19:07,040
 closeparen semicolon else printf openparen double quote bad type percent d and utype backslash n double quote comma utype closeparen semicolon.

388
01:19:07,040 --> 01:19:12,040
 Unions may occur in structures and arrays and vice versa.

389
01:19:12,040 --> 01:19:19,040
 The notion for accessing a member of a union in a structure or vice versa is identical to that for nested structures.

390
01:19:19,040 --> 01:19:38,040
 For example, in a structure array defined by struct open curly brace char star name semicolon int flags semicolon int utype semicolon union open curly brace int ival semicolon float fval semicolon

391
01:19:38,040 --> 01:19:51,040
