392
01:19:51,040 --> 01:20:07,040
 The variable ival is referred to as simtab sub i dot uval dot ival and the first character of the string pval by star simtab sub i dot uval dot pval.

393
01:20:07,040 --> 01:20:12,040
 In effect, a union is a structure in which all the members have offset zero.

394
01:20:12,040 --> 01:20:19,040
 The structure is big enough to hold the widest member and the alignment is appropriate for all types in the union.

395
01:20:19,040 --> 01:20:25,040
 As with structures, the only operations currently permitted on unions are accessing a member and taking the address.

396
01:20:25,040 --> 01:20:30,040
 Unions may not be assigned to, passed to functions, or returned by functions.

397
01:20:30,040 --> 01:20:36,040
 Pointers to unions can be used in a manner identical to pointers to structures.

398
01:20:36,040 --> 01:20:40,040
 Just as an aside, the above limitations on unions are just no longer accurate.

399
01:20:40,040 --> 01:20:46,040
 Like structures, modern C compilers can assign the contents of the union to another union variable.

400
01:20:46,040 --> 01:20:52,040
 You can also pass unions into functions by value and receive a union as the return type of a function.

401
01:20:52,040 --> 01:21:01,040
 The storage allocator in Chapter 8 shows how a union can be used to force a variable to be aligned on a particular kind of storage boundary.

402
01:21:01,040 --> 01:21:09,040
 Section 6.9. Type def. C provides a facility called type def for creating new data type names.

403
01:21:09,040 --> 01:21:20,040
 For example, the declaration type def space int space length semicolon makes the name length a synonym for int.

404
01:21:20,040 --> 01:21:27,040
 The type length can be used in declarations, CAS, etc. in exactly the same ways int can be.

405
01:21:27,040 --> 01:21:36,040
 Length len comma maxlen semicolon length star lengths open square bracket close square bracket semicolon.

406
01:21:36,040 --> 01:21:48,040
 Similar, the declaration type def char star string semicolon makes string a synonym for char star or a character pointer,

407
01:21:48,040 --> 01:22:00,040
 which then may be used in declarations like string p comma line ptr open square bracket lines close square bracket comma Alec open paren close paren semicolon.

408
01:22:00,040 --> 01:22:08,040
 Note that the type being declared in a type def appears in the position of a variable name, not right after the word type def.

409
01:22:08,040 --> 01:22:15,040
 Syntactically, type def is like the storage class, extern, static, etc.

410
01:22:15,040 --> 01:22:21,040
 We've used uppercase letters in these examples to emphasize the names.

411
01:22:21,040 --> 01:22:27,040
 A more complicated example, we could make type defs for the tree nodes shown earlier in the chapter.

412
01:22:27,040 --> 01:22:49,040
 Type def struct tnode open curly brace char star word semicolon int count semicolon struct tnode star left semicolon struct tnode star right semicolon close curly brace tree node comma star tree ptr.

413
01:22:49,040 --> 01:22:58,040
 This creates two new type keywords called tree node, which is a structure and tree ptr, which is a pointer to the structure.

414
01:22:58,040 --> 01:23:24,040
 Then the routine t alec could become tree ptr t alec open paren close paren open curly brace char star alec open paren close paren semicolon return open paren open paren tree ptr close paren alec open paren size of open paren tree node close paren close paren close paren semicolon close curly brace.

415
01:23:24,040 --> 01:23:31,040
 It should be emphasized that a type def declaration does not exactly create a new type in any sense.

416
01:23:31,040 --> 01:23:55,040
 It merely adds a new name for some existing types, nor are there any new semantics variables declared this way have exactly the same property as variables who whose declarations are spelled out explicitly.

417
01:23:55,040 --> 01:24:23,040
 For example, type def int open paren star pfi close paren open paren close paren semicolon creates a type pfi to mean pointer to a function returning integer, which can be used in context like pfi stir comp comma num comp comma swap in a sort program in Chapter 5.

418
01:24:23,040 --> 01:24:26,040
 There are two main reasons for using type def declaration.

419
01:24:26,040 --> 01:24:51,040
 The first is to parameterize program against portability problems. If type defs are used for the data types which may be machine dependent, only type defs need to change when the program is moved. One common situation is to use type def names for various integer quantities, and then make an appropriate set of choices of short int and long for each host machine.

420
01:24:51,040 --> 01:25:05,040
 The second purpose of type defs is to provide better documentation for a program type called tree PTR may be easier to understand than one declared only as a pointer to a complicated structure.

421
01:25:05,040 --> 01:25:19,040
 Finally, there's always the possibility that in the future, a compiler or some other program such as lint may make use of the information contained in type def declaration to perform some extra checking on the program.

